Aspect-Oriented Programming (AOP) in Spring Security allows you to modularize cross-cutting concerns like authentication, authorization, and auditing. Instead of scattering security checks across multiple methods, you define them once in an aspect and apply them consistently across your application.

🔹 Why Use AOP in Security?
Centralized Security → Define security rules in one place, apply them across services.

Cross-Cutting Concern Handling → Security is a classic cross-cutting concern (like logging, transactions).

Cleaner Code → Avoid repetitive security checks in every method.

Dynamic Control → Change or extend security logic without modifying business logic.
